Genera.— Nuclearia, Cienk. (37) (many nuclei; many
                    contractile vacuoles; body not permanently spherical, but amoeboid); Actinophrys, Ehr. (Fig. VII. 1; body spherical; pseudopodia
                    with an axial skeletal filament; central nucleus; one large contractile vacuole;
                    often forming colonies; A. sol, the Sun-animalcule); Actinosphaerium, Stein (Fig. VIII.; spherical body;
                    pseudopodia with axial filament; nuclei very numerous; contractile vacuoles 2 to
                    14); Actinolophus, F. E. Schulze (stalked).

